# Angular multi-file components

Every component in this app uses the standard three-file structure. Do not use inline templates or inline styles.

## Required file layout

```
feature-name/
  feature-name.component.ts
  feature-name.component.html
  feature-name.component.scss
```

## Component decorator

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-feature-name',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [...],
  templateUrl: './feature-name.component.html',
  styleUrl: './feature-name.component.scss',
})
export class FeatureNameComponent {}
```

## Rules

- Never use `template: \`...\`` or `styles: [...]` in `@Component`.
- Put all markup in `.html`; put component-scoped styles in `.scss` (Tailwind utility classes stay in HTML).
- Keep `.ts` for class logic, inputs/outputs, DI, and lifecycle hooks only.
- When creating a component, generate all three files together.
- Use `ng generate component` (CLI defaults are configured for this pattern).

## Do not

```typescript
// BAD — inline template
@Component({
  template: `<div>...</div>`,
})

// BAD — inline styles
@Component({
  styles: [`:host { display: block; }`],
})
```
